# Nuxt / Vue 3 Component Standards

## Nuxt UI First

Always prefer Nuxt UI components over building from scratch. Check the [Nuxt UI docs](https://ui.nuxt.com) before creating custom UI.

check nuxt-ui mcp component to get documentation and examples.
```vue
<!-- ❌ BAD: custom button from scratch -->
<button class="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded">Submit</button>

<!-- ✅ GOOD: Nuxt UI component -->
<UButton label="Submit" color="primary" />
```

Common Nuxt UI components to use:
- `UButton`, `UInput`, `USelect`, `UTextarea`, `UCheckbox`, `URadio`
- `UModal`, `USlideOver`, `UPopover`, `UTooltip`, `UDropdown`
- `UTable`, `UCard`, `UBadge`, `UAvatar`, `UAlert`
- `UForm`, `UFormField` for form validation
- `UNotifications` + `useToast()` for notifications
- `UIcon` for icons (uses Iconify)

## Composition API with TypeScript

Always use `<script setup lang="ts">`. Never use Options API.

```vue
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<script>
export default {
  data() { return { count: 0 } }
}
</script>

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<script setup lang="ts">
const count = ref<number>(0)
</script>
```

## Props & Emits

Always type props and emits explicitly.

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
interface Props {
  title: string
  count?: number
}

const props = withDefaults(defineProps<Props>(), {
  count: 0
})

const emit = defineEmits<{
  update: [value: number]
  close: []
}>()
</script>
```

## Composables

Extract reusable logic into composables under `composables/`. Prefix with `use`.

```ts
// composables/useMyFeature.ts
export function useMyFeature() {
  const state = ref(null)
  // logic...
  return { state }
}
```

## Auto-imports

Nuxt auto-imports Vue primitives and composables — do NOT manually import them:

```vue
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<script setup lang="ts">
import { ref, computed, onMounted } from 'vue'
import { useRoute } from 'vue-router'
</script>

<!-- ✅ GOOD — all auto-imported by Nuxt -->
<script setup lang="ts">
const route = useRoute()
const count = ref(0)
</script>
```

## Template Best Practices

- Use `v-bind` shorthand (`:prop`) and `v-on` shorthand (`@event`)
- Use `defineModel()` for two-way binding in Vue 3.4+
- Prefer `<template #slot>` named slots over `v-slot` shorthand for clarity
- Always set `:key` on `v-for` using a unique stable id, never the loop index

```vue
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<li v-for="(item, i) in items" :key="i">

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<li v-for="item in items" :key="item.id">
```

## Async Data Fetching

Use `useFetch` or `useAsyncData` (Nuxt composables), never raw `fetch`/`axios` in components.

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
const { data, status } = await useFetch('/api/items')
</script>
```

## File & Component Naming

- Component files: `PascalCase.vue` (e.g., `UserCard.vue`)
- Pages: `kebab-case.vue` inside `pages/` (e.g., `user-profile.vue`)
- Composables: `camelCase.ts` prefixed with `use` (e.g., `useUserProfile.ts`)


## Styling

Use Tailwind CSS for styling.

```css
/* ❌ BAD */
<style>
.my-component {
  background-color: red;
}
</style>
```

Do not add custom CSS classes to the components, use Tailwind CSS classes instead.
Do not use inline styles, use Tailwind CSS classes instead.

If you need to define custom colors, use the Tailwind CSS color variables.